The paper discusses optimization techniques for processing SPARQL queries, which are commonly used in the field of database management. Therefore, cs.DB (Database) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes novel optimization techniques using algorithms and analysis, which falls under the scope of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper deals with the procedural and structural aspects of SPARQL queries, which are related to cs.DS (Data Structures) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the proposed techniques, which is related to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
